@mistercrunch, I've added a migration script. Here's a dashboard that was saved before the migration:

<img width="1680" alt="screen shot 2018-07-06 at 6 45 00 pm" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1534870/42405658-a9d057ce-814e-11e8-826b-676c238048ba.png">

Note that:

- granularity is `month`;
- `num_period_compare` is 24 (months);
- `period_ratio_type` is "growth" (ie, `new/old - 1`).

After the migration:

<img width="1680" alt="screen shot 2018-07-06 at 8 04 02 pm" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1534870/42406214-c28016e8-8157-11e8-84a9-024953817714.png">

Now:

- `time_compare` is "2 years" (though it doesn't show in the dropdown since it's free form);
- `comparison_type` is "percentage" (same as "growth", just renamed).

It works after doing the following change (sorry for the massed up alignment, problems with github formatting):

